makeElectionAt(uint48,uint256).details: This function returns the list of validators that are will be responsible for block production in the next era.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

registerOperator().details: Operator must be registered in operator registry.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

disableOperator().notice: This function can be called only be operator themselves.

disableVault(address).notice: This function can be called only by the vault owner.

distributeOperatorRewards(address,uint25.notice: The function can be called only by the Router contract.

enableVault(address).notice: This function can be called only by the vault owner.

registerOperator().notice: This function can be called only be operator themselves.

unregisterVault(address).notice: This function can be called only by the vault owner.
